This paper is primarily focused on the analysis and detection of malware in mobile devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the design and implementation of a system for automatically collecting and managing a large volume of mobile malware, which involves software engineering principles (cs.SE). The system uses machine learning techniques to analyze and extract malicious code, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the need for efficient data retrieval and management, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and database systems (cs.DB).
